<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="e0273cbd-ed3a-4335-88f3-d85e07266603" >

    <p>Mentoring is an excellent way to learn as well as give back, share your experience, and guide students on their career journeys. The Ryerson Tri-Mentoring <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/studentlife/trimentoring/about/career-mentoring/">Career Mentoring Program</a> will help you make a connection with a current Ryerson student.</p> 
<p>A Career Mentor is:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>A guide and adviser to a third/fourth or final year student (Career Mentee), providing insight into a particular industry sector or type of profession.</li> 
</ul> 
<ul> 
 <li>Provides constructive criticism and encouragement to their mentee as they progress towards their goals.</li> 
 <li>Culturally sensitive and possesses strong interpersonal skills.<br> &nbsp;</li> 
</ul> 
<p>For more information, please visit the <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/studentlife/trimentoring/about/career-mentoring/">Career Mentoring Program</a>.</p>
    





